org.apache.logging.log4j.layout.template.json.resolver

Class LevelResolver

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.logging.log4j.layout.template.json.resolver.LevelResolver
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    EventResolver, TemplateResolver<org.apache.logging.log4j.core.LogEvent>

    public final class LevelResolver
extends Object
implements EventResolver
    Level resolver.

    Configuration

     config         = field , [ severity ]
 field          = "field" -> ( "name" | "severity" )
 severity       = severity-field
 severity-field = "field" -> ( "keyword" | "code" )

    Examples

    Resolve the level name: 
     {
   "$resolver": "level",
   "field": "name"
 }
    Resolve the severity keyword: 
     {
   "$resolver": "level",
   "field": "severity",
   "severity": {
     "field": "keyword"
   }
 }

 Resolve the severity code:

 
     {
   "$resolver": "level",
   "field": "severity",
   "severity": {
     "field": "code"
   }
 }
